CHANGES AFTER v2.03 (Release 03-10-1999)
----------------------------------------
- Added support for the 'RealSpectrum' Spectrum emulator from Ramsoft.

CHANGES AFTER v2.02 (Release 30-05-1999)
----------------------------------------
- Linked Workbench! v2.71.8 with the following enhancements:
  - Solved a severe window linking bug;
  - Changeable mouse speed settings;
- Rewrote small portions of the 'Search for Games' routine;
- Added option 'MouseSpeedSetting' to SGD.INI
- Increased stack size from 32Kb to 64Kb.
- Added basic support for `.FDI' files;
- Added support for the Russian Spectrum emulator from Vladimir Yudin.

CHANGES AFTER v2.01 (Release 11-01-1999)
----------------------------------------
- Linked Workbench! v2.71.7 with the following enhancements:
  - Two minor bugfixes;
- Added database field `Author(s)' with a width of 100 characters.
  !!! ALL DATABASES CREATED WITH EARLIER VERSIONS ARE INVALID NOW !!!
  Added auto-conversion of databases;
  This field gets criterion identifier `AU' and print object code `S';
- The TZX Archive Info Block editor got import and export buttons for this new
  Author(s) field.
- Added combined criterion `BY' which searches both Publisher and Authors;
- Transformed field `Improveable' into `Origin'. The search identifier for this
  field has changed from (bool) `IM' to (single ASCII char) `OR'.
  Old (bool) values `Y' are transformed into `B' (for Bad version);
- Added option `Force Snap Joystick' to the configuration window;
- Updated support for Z80:
  - The new v4.00 accepts TZX files,
  - It is now enough to copy the file Z80STUB.EXE from the SGD directory into
    the directory where the DOS version of Z80 is installed. This stub will
    automatically be selected when Windows 95 and up has been detected and this
    behavior allows a single SGD.INI that runs correctly in both DOS/Windows.
  - WinZ80 treats command line parameters entirely differently;
- Typing a longer match string than the field length in a (alphanumeric) search
  criterion could crash SGD;
- Added existance support for .DSK files (X128 and ZX-32);
- Several more optimizations;
- (Full source is now over 2.91Mb and 46,000 lines of C/asm!)

CHANGES AFTER v2.00 (Release 19-10-1998)
----------------------------------------
- Linked Workbench! v2.71.6 with the following enhancements:
  - After calling an external program, SGD will continue, but the mouse is kept
    hidden until it moves or a key is pressed (in the previous release, SGD
    would be stopped until the mouse was moved);
  - Error reporting when spawning an external application (eg. an emulator) was
    incorrect. System errors weren't displayed at all anymore;
  - Solved a new timer error, caused by a bug in Windows 98;
  - Sometimes the timer would run wildly (Windows), resulting in hefty screen
    FLASH rates;
  - The video init tries to bypass a crash bug caused by the BIOS of some
    video cards that badly behave under Windows (eg. S3 Trio64V+);
  - Added check for WindowNT. If detected, all soundcard options are disabled;
  - In EditButtons and InputBoxes, <CTRL><P> is remapped to a pound sign (`œ'),
    since this character cannot otherwise be generated on non-English keyboards;
- The `Save' function in the BASIC listing window would save in the wrong text
  format (ComboWindow format rather than expanded format);
- When selecting a language or emulator override, the drop-down window would be
  partly overwritten if a FLASHing screen was displayed at that time;
- The configuration option to select the ASCII editor did not start a
  FileRequester anymore;
- Spectrum header filenames with TABs in them would let the rest of the line in
  a combo window clip out of the window;
- All paths in SGD.INI are internally converted to upper case, otherwise DOS
  won't find your screenshots, info files, etc.
- Added option `AllFilesInOneDir' to the configuration file (default Off).
  If turned on, all extra files (screenshots, info, pokes and inlays) are
  searched for in the game's directory itself rather than the normal subdirs.
  Useful for several emulation CD's!
- Updated support for the emulator `R80'. You need at least v0.04 now!
  Added support for .TRD files and joystick preselection;
- Added (by popular demand) additional criterion (de)selection using '+' or '-'
  as first character;
- Added memory types `+2/+2A' (value 130), `+3' (value 131) and `Pentagon'
  (value 228, printed as `Pentag'). Emulators that know these models (X128, R80
  and Warajevo) are started up accordingly;
- Added checks for reversed TZX version numbers (caused by a bug in an older
  MakeTZX version) and added an option to repair the number;
- (Full source is now over 2.90Mb and 45,900 lines of C/asm!)

CHANGES AFTER v1.37 (Release 08-05-1998)
----------------------------------------
!!! IMPORTANT: THE 16-BIT VERSION HAS BEEN DISCONTINUED !!!
- Linked Workbench! v2.71.5 with the following enhancements:
  - Solved a very nasty crash bug, caused by a sometimes-not-initialized
    variable!
  - The TMP directory was stored incorrectly and used the current directory
    instead, making the program very unsuitable to be used on CD or on a drive
    with little space;
  - The ReInitComboWindow routine did not reset the slider StepRate;
    (load a large database, then a small one and the slider moved trash around)
  - The timer value would fallover if a timer interrupt occured at the moment
    the value was read. This affected mouse click handling and screen FLASHing;
  - Empty lines in a file were skipped by the FileViewRequester;
  - When restoring the startup video mode, mode bit 7 is forced 0 to make sure
    the screen is cleared;
  - Some other minor corrections;
  - After spawning an application while running under Win95 and up, the mouse is
    kept hidden until moved, to avoid the screen corruption caused by Windows's
    bad (un)focus handling;
  - Executables without preceeding path would not search the PATH variable
    anymore;
- Added memory type `USR0' (value 129), for 128K programs that must be loaded
  in `USR 0' mode;
- Turned the memory type selector from a sequence to a drop-down window;
- Added option `QuitInTextMode' to the configuration file to force (color) text
  mode on program exit (turned off per default);
- Added option `AutoLoadTapes' to the configuration file and window, which will
  automatically load tape files in emulators Z80, X128 and Warajevo;
- Added files `LOAD48.Z80', `LOAD128.Z80' and `LOADUSR0.Z80' to the distribution
  for this purpose;
- Added option `Always Select Game' to the configuration window;
- Added option `ZX-Editor Path' to the configuration file and window;
- Added option `Always Use ZX-Editor' to the configuration file and window;
- Your game info files may now be written with the ZX-Editor. Such files have
  priority over ASCII (.TXT) files.
- Reordered the configuration window for better grouping;
- Added current entry number (line number) to the far right of the totals box
  (in the `Selected Game' window, right below the entries);
- TZX `Custom Info - Instructions' and `Custom Info - Spectrum Screen' blocks
  can now be viewed;
- TZX `Custom Info - POKEs' blocks can now be viewed/edited;
- Added full support for the TZX v1.12 extensions;
- Added options `GIFViewerPath', `GIFViewerOptions', `JPGViewerPath' and
  `JPGViewerOptions' to the configuration file to handle the new TZX v1.12
  block `Custom Info - Picture';
- Added wizards to setup the above new configuration options;
- Added button `Inlay' to the main screen to view a game's inlay in .JPG or
  .GIF format (see SGD.DOC);
- Added full support for the new Spectrum emulator `R80';
- Added full support for the Russian Spectrum emulator `ZX Spectrum' from
  Nikolay Shalayev;
- Added very basic support for .TRD files (X128 and Russian only);
- TAPER can now also be called on Z80 and SNA files! You need at least
  TAPER v2.03 for this feature;
- X128 and Warajevo also have the ability to load a snap and a tape at the same
  time (for multi-part games that continue loading from the tape file);
- Warajevo supports `Lunter-TAP' files natively since v2.0;
- Warajevo can also load non-native image types .SNA, .VOC, .TZX, .SP and .LTP;
- Z80 snapshots v3 reported the hardware types `48K + SamRam' and `48K + M.G.T.'
  reversed due to an error in the documentation of Z80;
- The configuration option `FollowSlider' was not set correctly at startup;
- The `Extension Links' incorrectly had a higher priority than an emulator
  override;
- Block graphics were printed rotated by 1 when saving out BASIC listings;
- Added files Z80STUB.EXE and Z80STUB.PIF to the distribution to work around
  the crash problem of Z80 in Win95 and up (see SGD.DOC section 20.1);
- (Full source is now over 2.90Mb and 45,600 lines of C/asm!)

CHANGES AFTER v1.36 (Release 28-02-1998)
----------------------------------------
- Linked Workbench! vX.71.2 with the following enhancements:
  - Watcom appeared to report system error messages from the wrong table.
    This job has been taken over;
  - A combo window could occasionally have a vertical slider that was drawn
    through the bottom of the slider bar after resizing the window;
  - The `Ok' button in the FileRequester is now (un)ghosted while editing the
    filename field. No need to press <TAB> or <ENTER> afterward anymore!
  - The `Refresh' button in the FileRequester will force a file system commit
    before rereading the directory (appeared to be needed for Win95 and up);
  - The FileViewRequester would go back to the start of the file when resizing;
  - The FileViewRequester has been adjusted so that also text files created on a
    Macintosh are displayed correctly (single CR as end-of-line delimiter);
  - A view-only combo window (eg. the FileViewRequester) would generate a
    General Protection Fault when <CURSOR UP> was pressed when at the top of the
    file;
  - Starting the menu strip while an edit button was active always started
    the menu as through pressing <F9>.
  - The LocalMouseHiding routine has been tightened, eliminating the possible
    (small) screen corruption;
  - A 3-button mouse can be simulated from a 2-button mouse using a
    `chord middle' option as in several OSes;
- Updated the entry sorting algorithm to allow multi-level sorting: the order is
  game name, publisher, year, memory type, filename;
- Entries that did not have a filename attached would stay red even if a
  filename was provided at a later time (until reloading of the database);
- The selection bar would be invalid if you did `Add' and then `Delete' again
  without filling in a game name;
- The selection criterion would not be reparsed when changing the boolean
  buttons `Original Screen', `Improve' or `AY-Sound';
- The EdPokes window did not work at all anymore and would create garbage files;
- Changes in the BASIC listing window:
  - The window lost its `Save' button when it was resized;
  - The `Save' button starts a FileRequester, defaulting to the same directory
    where the file is located;
  - The listing would go back to the start when resizing;
- The selection criterion `LN' (Language) did not work at all;
- The option `ForceSnapJoystick' would generate an invalid path, making the
  option useless;
- The filetype of the currently selected game would occasionally be incorrect
  when changing emulator in the configuration, until you reselected the game;
- Added option `Emulate3rdMouseButton' to the configuration file;
- (Full source is now over 2.74Mb and 43,100 lines of C/asm!)

CHANGES AFTER v1.35 (Release 11-02-1998)
----------------------------------------
- Linked Workbench! vX.71.1 with the following enhancements:
  - Solved a bug where characters were occasionally not printed in a combo
