- (Full source is now over 2.72Mb and 42,750 lines of C/asm!)

CHANGES AFTER v1.32 (Release 25-09-1997)
----------------------------------------
- Linked Workbench! vX.71.0 with the following enhancements:
  - v1.71.0 is the usual 16-bit real mode version ('286 code, XMS based),
    v2.71.0 is a conversion to 32-bit protected mode ('386+, DPMI based);
  - Solved some major memory related bugs;
  - Small increase of overall speed for the 16-bit version,
    Major increase of overall speed for the 32-bit version;
  - Own local mouse hiding routine works in Win95 as well and speeds up a lot;
  - The 'NoLocalMouseHiding' flag is no longer needed for Win95;
  - Win96 (OSR2) and up were incorrectly reported (but correctly detected);
  - Rewrote window drag routine to gain some more speed;
  - Added HardwareError button `Fail';
  - HardwareError button `Abort' aborts the entire program rather than the
    failing operation!
    This only goes for the 32-bit version.
  - Sometimes the global keyboard buffer was not cleared when a window where the
    key came from was closed;
  - Changes in the FileRequester:
    - The FileRequester would produce a FatalError if an empty path was passed
      (e.g. an unset configuration option);
    - Deletion of a single file produced an error unless you explicitely
      selected it first;
    - Due to a problem in Watcom C, the drives (at the bottom of the list) do no
      longer report their volume label, but are listed as `<Drive>' instead;
      This only goes for the 32-bit version.
    - <DEL> will delete the selected file(s) (same as the `Delete' button);
  - Drop-down windows could not be controlled with the keyboard;
  - (Combo window) <CTRL><INSRT> did not work at all;
  - The menu strip is fully controlable with the keyboard;
  - Added mechanism to bail out on recursed faults (reported as double faults).
    This produced a complete crash of the entire machine before;
  - Solved file handle leak in the font reader;
- Since v1.35, SGD is available in both 16-bit real mode and 32-bit protected
  mode. The 16-bit version no longer has the menu option `Call TAPER', as this
  requires a '386 and up.
- The (bogus) error return code from `X128' is ignored. You no longer have to
  press a key to continue after running this emulator;
- Major speed gain when loading databases under Win95. They load near instantly;
- <DEL> will delete the currently selected game;
- Games were not auto-selected (if that was turned on in the configuration) when
  using <CTRL><CRUP> and <CTRL><CRDN> (browse selected entries);
- Screenshot creation from the menu strip did not work for TZX files;
- Solved file handle leak when handling TZX files;
- An error line ">>>>> Missing datablock" would corrupt the next line;
- The right (game information) window was not cleaned up if the last entry in a
  database was deleted or a new database was started;
- Added memory type `16', for 16K games;
- Added option `PhonebookSorting' to the configuration file;
- Added support for TZX up to v1.11;
- Updated file HARDWARE.INC to suit TZX v1.11;
- (Full source is now over 2.45Mb and 40,200 lines of C/asm!)

