CHANGES AFTER v1.25 (Release 24-01-1997)
-----------------------------------------
- Linked Workbench! v1.70.0 with the following enhancements:
  - Completely rewrote the combo window virtual memory handler. The entire
    entry table now resides in XMS, so no matter how many entries are in a
    combo window, all conventional memory is left alone!
  - Adjusted PrintComboEntries to re-align the window when entries had been
    deleted from the end of the combo list, so that an empty bottom would
    appear;
  - Exported mouse timers to allow user configuration;
  - Gave the FileViewRequester resize properties;
  - Moved the FollowSlider combo flag into the operating system - it now
    adjusts all combo windows (e.g. in FileViewRequesters);
  - Increased minimal SliderLength to 5 pixels (was 3);
  - Solved some bugs in print attribute handling;
  - Added print blink attributes '{L1' and '{L2' ('}L' to turn it off);
- Reduced all memory constraints for combo windows. The maximum number of
  games to handle is set to a vast 32767 per database.
  This also means that you will always be able to see info files to their full
  extent (no more truncation unless there are over 32767 lines :-);
- You can now use `{L1' (ink-blink) and `{L2' (invert-blink) sequences in your
  game info files.
  This feature also works for game names and poke descriptions;
  These entries are still sorted correctly and ignored when using the
  typed-name feature or printing;
- Colors in Spectrum token expansion were in VGA order rather than Spectrum;
- Print attributes in info files are now active until you turn them off
  (Previously, they were turned off when the end of the line was reached);
- Added description of the (current) database format to SGD.DOC;
- You weren't allowed to create a .GIF file from a screenshot inside an .SLT
  file;
- Boolean selection criteria with value 'N' were never true (e.g. 'OS=N');
- Some Spectrum tokens had bad padding;
- Spectrum UDG characters are now different from normal characters;
- Added button `Help' to the main screen, which allows you to view SGD.DOC;
- If you have exactly 1 entry in your database, SGD would produce a floating
  point exception error when running some menu options;
- Added extra checks so that device "C[none]:" (as in marked floppies) will no
  longer occur;
- Functions `ReadConfig' and `WriteConfig' didn't ask for your SGD floppy when
  running off a floppy. Instead, the config was written on whatever floppy
  happened to be in the drive (reading produced an error in that case);
- You can now select which GameDir directories are to be searched when chosing
  the menu entry `Find New Games';
- Optionally, `Find New Games' will fill in the file name for a game name;
- Added menu option `Search for new games', which automatically searches an
  entire file tree;
- Added options `DoubleClickInterval' and `InitialContPushDelay' to the
  configuration file to allow adjustment of the mouse timers;
- When using `Z80' or `Warajevo' with anything but .Z80 or .SLT files, the
  selected joystick will be the (first) one you selected in the Game
  Information Area;
- Added option `ForceSnapJoystick' to the configuration file to patch the
  selected game (into the TMP directory) to allow the above option for .Z80
  and .SLT type files as well (all emulators);
- Added possibility to select which fields (and in what order) will be
  printed. This is done through a 'Select' button in the Print requester;
- Added option `PrintedFields' to the configuration file to save this setup;
- Added option `View BASIC-part' to the menu strip under `Entry', which shows
  the BASIC part from a snapshot file;
- You can now select a PROG block in a TAP window, in which case the BASIC
  listing can be viewed;
- 'Z80' appears to have a 'no sound' switch after all. I must have been blind;
- (Full source is now over 2Mb and 32000 lines of C/asm!)

CHANGES AFTER v1.24 (Release 05-01-1997)
