- Made the database backup function work :)
- Shrinked printed entries when printing the database - field seperation is now
  1 space in stead of 2; each line is now 126 characters;
- Shrinked the databasefile itself as well; each line is now (always!) 129
  characters;
- Added database fields `FileSize', `Orig Scr' and `Improve';
  !!! ALL DATABASES CREATED WITH EARLIER VERSIONS ARE INVALID NOW !!!
- Added selection criterion `PB', which tests the `Play' bit of the game in
  the entry table;
- Added selection criteria `OS' and `IM' for `Orig Screen' and `IMprove';
- Updated command line switch -C:
  C1 is the old convert flag (pre-1.08)
  C2 is the new convert flag (pre-1.10)
- Renamed button `Ok' in configuration window to `Save';
- Renamed button `Cancel' in configuration window to `Reload';
- Added button `Try' in configuration window - is now the default button;
- Reversed displayed order of `Save' and `Reload' - positive values right;
- Improved corruption test when loading a database;
- Spectrum Screen and List output is now explicitely removed when the
  button is released;
- When putting a screen returns an error, the black border is no longer
  printed;
- Non-crunched (v1.45) Z80 snapshots took the wrong buffer to display the
  spectrum screen - fixed;
- Added default paths for the emulators if no path was given in the
  configuration: `Z80.EXE' for Z80 and `JPP.EXE' for JPP - both in the same
  directory as SGD;
- Forgot to remove tape/microdrive index on several more occations - fixed;
- Introduced memory failure when drawing spectrum screen from a TAP file in
  previous version - fixed;
- Fixed CreateTAPCatalog, where HEAD blocks were now reported with length
  2 bytes too much - blocks with length < 2 are now reported as being noise;
- Added some sort of index in SGD.DOC;

CHANGES AFTER v1.08 (Release 30-01-1996)
----------------------------------------
- Linked Workbench! v1.60.0 with the following enhancements:
  - Added code to compact far heap on combo window reinitialization;
  - Changed key <DEL> for toggling the selection for a combo entry into
    <SHIFT><INS>, as it should have been :)
  - Added check for <CTRL> key when selecting a combo entry with the mouse:
    this will toggle the selection bit(s) for all entries in the range from
    the last selected entry up to the currently selected entry;
    Didn't add a keyequivalent (<CTRL><INS>) for it!
  - Solved memory leak in ReInitComboWindow;
  - Added some sanity checks to the SwapOut function;
  - Put the cursor one pixel left in edit buttons, where it should be;
  - Added percentage requester to the CopyFile requester;
  - Solved problem where `Delete' in a FileRequester would sometimes remove
    the wrong file from the list (but the correct one from disk);
  - Adjusted SortEntry to re-align the window when entries had been deleted
    from the end of the combo list, so that an empty bottom would appear;
  - Removed stale function parameters and variables;
- Decreased stack size 4K;
- Decreased memory needs;
- Streamlined memory usage when viewing screens;
- Removed bug where the `Create GIF' menu entry was incorrectly unghosted
  when you start a new or open an existing database;
- Removed a bug where table pre-allocation for the game select window might
  sometimes allocate room for -1 entries...
- Changed meaning of an empty selection string - previously it meant that ALL
  entries matched, it now means that NO entries match;
- Inverted game selection colors: selected games are now with cyan background.
  (I didn't like it from the beginning, but it was easier to implement then)
- Forgot to remove a tape/microdrive index when one is on the screen and you
  start a new or open an existing database;
- Changed name handling of temporary database files - they are no longer always
  called `GAMES.TMP', but keep their database name with extenion `.TMP';
- Removed a bug where printfiles would always be placed in the current
  directory, no matter where the database itself was;
- Added option `BackupDatabase' to the configuration file, which will copy the
  `old' database (once) to a backupfile before writing a new one;
- Added menu option `Duplicate entry';
- Adjusted Import function so that the first imported entry will be
  automatically selected;
- Added some more memory probes to allow a graceful FatalError in stead of a
  system crash ;)

CHANGES AFTER v1.07 (Release 26-11-1995)
----------------------------------------
- Linked Workbench! v1.59.1 with the following enhancements:
  - Added code to allow graceful release of the mouse driver if the driver
    version is 7.00 or up - the mouse is now `re-usable' as it should be :)
  - Added default key to the window structure, which is selected if an edit
    button is ended with an <ENTER> (<TAB> still does the same);
  - Removed a bug in the delayed mouse event handler, which lost the button
    if too much time had passed;
  - Added check for RIL residence, added error if not;
  - Added mouse flag `SnapToDefaultButton', which moves the mouse to the
    default button together with the DefaultKey change;
  - Added mouse flag `UseGeniusScreenUpdate', which uses the `old' style
    Genius driver call to DefineScreenRegionForUpdating;
  - Added code in DefineScreenRegionForUpdating to allow for a changed mouse
    hotspot location - solves all remaining mouse hiding problems;
  - Changed the QuestionRequester, so that the negative option is the default
    rather than the positive option.
  - Removed double-click timer overrun, which caused any next click after the
    second to be treated as a double-click as well;
  - Removed a bug in the BF_FITDIR flag at button startup, where it was simply
    ignored;
  - Changed the edit button handler, so that all buttons with the BF_FITDIR
    flag set will convert all lower case keys to upper case;
  - Removed a bug in the edit button handler, where <CTRL><DEL> would not
    delete the contents, if the cursor was at the end of the string;
  - Changed the FileRequester to stay in drives mode if you select a drive
    which returns a hardware error and you choose abort;
  - Changed printing of combo select entries: each entry is now one pixel
    wider at both ends, the selection bar is printed while printing the
    entries and is one pixel less high - improved in speed and no more flicker;
  - Changed XMS allocation manager to (re)allocate XMS memory chunkwise - this
    reduces allocation requests and speeds up the management;
  - Changed conventional memory allocation manager to (re)allocate combo
    window tables chunkwise - this solves most of the extreme memory
    fragmentation and speeds up all memory related operations;
  - Added code to keep the far heap optimized - solves the rest of the memory
    fragmentation problems;
  - Removed a bug in the mouse handler where it sometimes remembered a button
    press but forgot the location;
  - Removed `%' character expansion bug in the FileViewRequester;
  - Changed newline-handling in the FileViewRequester, so that non-DOS files
    (i.e. Unix-style) can be displayed as well;
  - Adjusted ComboWindow key handler, so that cursor/page/<INS>/<DEL> keys are
    no longer consumed if also a <CTRL> or <ALT> key was pressed;
  - Removed a bug in low-memory handler, where the meaning of the buttons was
    reversed;
  - Added buttons `Rename', `Copy' and `Delete' to the FileRequester to allow
    some simple file management;
  - Added Requesters: InputRequester and CopyFile;
  - Reprints edit button contents reformatted at button startup when the
    button contains a path name;
  - Removed printing bug in combo windows, where a byte was lost if the first
    char started at bit 7 in video ram;
  - Removed printing bug in combo windows, where empty `{' and `}' characters
    were incorrectly expanded when sliding horizontally;
  - Made XMSAllAllocated return the correct value :)
  - Changed key <CTRL><ALT><F12> (for GIF screendump) to <CTRL><PRTSC>;
  - Changed key <CTRL><ALT><F10> (for Panic shutdown) to <CTRL><ALT><ESC>;
  - Optimized GIF creation algorithm some more;
  - Rewrote ChunkyToPlanar routine (used for pictures in buttons/requesters);
    major speed gain;
  - Optimized menu system for better memory usage;
  - Changed QuestionRequester to support 4 buttons (Yes/No/Cancel/All);
  - Added combo entry selection with <SHIFT> or middle mouse button;
  - Added key-equivalent <DEL> for it;
  - Added middle button check in sliderset; does the same as pressing <SHIFT>
    while on the slider;
- Removed a bug when using a database on a different volume than SGD, which
  caused the fatal error: `Could not install new database: Cross-link device'
- Added field to each database entry, which holds the location of the latest
  found location of this game (an index into the GamePath array). No extra
  memory is needed for this - file resolvation is now A LOT quicker!
  !!! ALL DATABASES CREATED WITH EARLIER VERSIONS ARE INVALID NOW !!!
- Added command line switch `-c' to use compatibility mode, which converts the
  database to this new format, to solve the above problem;
- Added command line switch `-g' to activate the `old' style Genius driver
  calls;
- Added command line switch `-p' to disable the load/save percentage bar;
- Added option `SnapMouseDefault' to the configuration file to activate the
  new mouse parameter;
- Added this option and the game editor path to the configuration window;
- Added option `GIFPath' to the configuration file; this will be used as the
  directory where Spectrum screen images will be stored;
- Changed handling of the path to the emulator itself. The filename is now
  also included in the path, so that you don't have to use the default
  `Z80.EXE' or `JPP.EXE', but any executable (including batch files);
- Reparses the selection criterion after reloading the database now;
- Added variable to remember last used path in a FileRequester, to easier
  add games from the same (new) directory to the database;
- Removed FileRequester bug which ignored the change when the same filename
  was returned, but in a different directory;
- Stores current entry when parsing a changed criterion - this entry is now
  also considered while parsing;
- Adjusts count of matching games when deleting an entry;
- Added keys <CTRL><CRUP> to move one selected game up and <CTRL><CRDN> to
  move one selected game down;
- Added LPT0: in the configuration, which prints the database to a file;
- Solved memory leak in ReadConfig routine;
- Removed bug in CreateTAPCatalog, where HEAD blocks were reported with length
  2 bytes too little;
- Added menuing system a la Amiga; The right mouse button is now used for the
  menu and is no longer used to start the selected game;
- Added font file `8X10N.FNT' for the menu strip;
- Added possibility to partially print or save a database;
- Added possibility to merge databases or change database;
- Added possibility to start a new, empty, database;
- Added possibility to resort the database;
- Added possibility to invert or delete all selected entries at once;
- Added possibility to create a GIF file of the current Spectrum screen image
  (which will be stored in the `GIFPath' directory);
- Renamed button `Write' to `Save'. It uses hot-key <ALT><S>;
- Changed hot-key for button `Shell' to <ALT><H>;
- Made some functions global to provide better code re-useability;
- Removed a bug where on some error conditions a PercentageRequester was not
  removed from the screen;
- Added current databasename to the bottom of the information window;
- (Full source is now over 1.2Mb and 19000 lines of C/asm)

CHANGES AFTER v1.06 (Release 09-11-1995)
----------------------------------------
- Linked Workbench! v1.58.8 with the following enhancements:
  - Finally, changed combo selection box into an inverted bar;
  - Added auto-advance for edit buttons - pressing <TAB> while in an active
    edit button does the same as pressing <ENTER>; the new contents are
    accepted and the next button is elected (as the <TAB> handling before);
  - Added auto-select for edit buttons - when an edit button is elected due to
    the (new) <TAB> handler, the button is immediately started up;
  - Added cursor-repositioning for edit buttons - click in an active edit 
    button to set the cursor to that location (ignored previously);
  - Removed cursor-init bug in edit buttons - if the button is activated by
    the keyboard, the cursor is now always set at the end of the contents (it
    was set at the mouse-x, as for mouse-activation, previously);
  - Added typed-name feature to the FileRequester, linked to the filename box;
  - Added FileRequester file pre-selection - if a filename is given, this name
    will be auto-selected. If either no name is given or it is not found, the
    first file in the list is selected;
  - Changed QuestionRequester to support 3 buttons (Yes/No/Cancel);
  - Changed blanker routine - display is no longer copied and blanked,
    but the video refresh pin is disabled (if not supported (true EGA), the
    palette is blanked). Saves XMS and provides instant blanking/restoring.
  - Removed a bug in the FileRequester, which caused a void CustomPicture to
    be drawn if the selected filename did not exist (and one had to);
  - Removed some `changed directory' bugs;
- Changed `EdInfo' handler to create the INFO directory before starting the
  editor if the directory did not exist yet (omitting this caused random error
  messages depending on the used editor);
- Added Cancel possibility when pressing `Quit' and the database has been
  changed;
- When you press the `Delete' button, the name of the game is now also printed
  in the confirmation box;
- Added command line option to be able to use a different database than the
  default `GAMES.DAT'
- Action buttons are now all ghosted as appropriate;
- Removed all XMS errors when dealing with an empty database;
- Changing any entry field in an empty database now implicitely adds an entry;
- Added a troubleshooting section in `SGD.DOC'

